Male genitalia (
Figs. 12–15
): Epandrium blackish brown with long brown setulae, without a pair of bandshaped sclerites, but hyaline membrane present around the anus with some spinous setulae; surstylus basally broad with short spinous setulae, distally narrowed. Mesolobus long, 6 times as long as wide, rod-like in dorsal view, with 2 pairs of setulae. Gonites arranged in a row; postgonite 1.2 times as long as pregonite, incurved distally with pointed apex, with some sensory setulae, basally round; pregonite basally broad and round, distally narrowed; basiphallus longer than wide, cylindrical; distiphallus cylindrical, membranous, extended to basal margin of pregonite; phallapodeme long, extended near base of basiphallus, with basal stalk broad in lateral view. Hypandrium narrow, without two basal rounded projections.

External characteristics similar to male. Female genitalia (
Figs. 16–18
): epiproct pentagonal, as long as wide, with 2 long setae; hypoproct long, apically round with long stout setae. Cercus long and stout with some long setae.
